{"id":32627,"date":"2019-07-03T18:15:20","date_gmt":"2019-07-03T14:15:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=32627"},"modified":"2019-07-03T18:15:20","modified_gmt":"2019-07-03T14:15:20","slug":"how-many-gods-worship-now","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/03\/how-many-gods-worship-now\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Idolatry: How many gods do you worship now?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>\u2018Imran ibn Husayn reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said to my father, \u201c<strong>O Husayn, how many gods do you worship today?<\/strong>\u201d My father said, \u201cSeven. Six on earth and one in heaven.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>In which of them do you depend for your most ardent hopes and concerns?<\/strong>\u201d He said, \u201cThe one in heaven.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>O Husayn, if you accept Islam, I will teach you two words to benefit you.<\/strong>\u201d Later when Husayn had embraced Islam, he said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, teach me the two words you promised to me.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Say: O Allah, inspire me with guidance and protect me from the evil of my ego.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3483<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em>Jayyid<\/em> (very good) according to Ibn Hajar<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u0650\u0645\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u062d\u064f\u0635\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064f \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0644\u0650\u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a <strong>\u064a\u064e\u0627 \u062d\u064f\u0635\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u06